LOGS
Event ID: 4624
What it means: successful login (type 5 – system process)
Why it's important: helps distinguish between legitimate and suspicious logins. The SOC monitors for repeated or unusual login types (for example, type 10 – remote, may indicate RDP).
  Event ID: 1012
Source: DNS Client Events
What it means: The DNS service was unable to read the local hosts file
Why it's important: May indicate DNS issues or an attempt to modify the hosts file—potentially important for SOCs when analyzing network anomalies
Event ID: 8303
Source: System Restore
What it means: Error creating or verifying a restore point (shadow copy)
Why it's important: This could simply be a system error, but it's also used by attackers to delete restore points before ransomware encryption.
